<function>

access:   public

name: regex

param: mixed, $value

param: string, $expr

param: bool, $blank, false

return: bool

</function>

Validate a value against a regular expression.

* Parameters:

 * mixed //$value//: The value to validate.

 * string //$expr//: The regular expression to validate against.

 * bool //$blank//: Allow blank values to be valid.

* Returns bool: True if the value matches the expression, false if not.

Validate a value against a regular expression.

Uses [[php preg_match]] to compare the value against the given
regular epxression.